{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Sr37mL7iGiULgcVYn7hDjw","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]\n3\tlastStep: 8\n4\tstatus: 'complete'\n5\tcompletedAt: '2026-04-02'\n6\tinputDocuments:\n7\t  - prd-evaluator-redesign.md\n8\t  - research/domain-harness-design-long-running-agents-research-2026-04-01.md\n9\t  - research/technical-ai-agent-verification-testing-research-2026-03-16.md\n10\t  - research/technical-workflow-engine-implementation-research-2026-04-02.md\n11\t  - architecture.md (v1 architecture, brownfield context)\n12\tworkflowType: 'architecture'\n13\tproject_name: 'codeharness'\n14\tuser_name: 'BMad'\n15\tdate: '2026-04-02'\n16\t---\n17\t\n18\t# Architecture Decision Document\n19\t\n20\t_This document builds collaboratively through step-by-step discovery. Sections are appended as we work through each architectural decision together._\n21\t\n22\t## Project Context Analysis\n23\t\n24\t### Requirements Overview\n25\t\n26\t**Functional Requirements:** 43 FRs across 10 capability areas — Workflow Definition (6), Agent Configuration (6), Workflow Configuration (3), Workflow Execution (8), Adversarial Verification (5), Feedback Loop (3), Circuit Breaker (4), Observability (2), CLI Commands (4), Legacy Removal (2).\n27\t\n28\t**Non-Functional Requirements:** 18 NFRs across Performance (5), Reliability (5), Integration (4), Code Quality (4). Architecture-critical NFRs: crash recovery via state persistence (NFR6-8), programmatic agent dispatch only (NFR11), optional observability (NFR14).\n29\t\n30\t**Scale & Complexity:**\n31\t- Primary domain: Developer tooling (CLI + plugin)\n32\t- Complexity level: High\n33\t- Estimated architectural components: ~10\n34\t- Cross-cutting concerns: config resolution chain, trace ID propagation, crash recovery, evaluator isolation\n35\t\n36\t### Technical Constraints & Dependencies\n37\t\n38\t- Runtime: Node.js (TypeScript)\n39\t- Dependencies: `commander`, `yaml`, `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`\n40\t- Execution substrate: Agent SDK `query()` — async generator, session management, JSON schema output\n41\t- State: Single `workflow-state.yaml` in repo (beads-level simplicity)\n42\t- Evaluator isolation: Separate workspace, no source code, Docker container for artifact\n43\t- Docker: Required for evaluator but graceful degradation if missing (Journey 5)\n44\t\n45\t### Cross-Cutting Concerns\n46\t\n47\t1. **Config resolution** — every agent/workflow dispatch resolves embedded → user → project patches\n48\t2. **Trace ID propagation** — generated per iteration, injected into agent prompts, correlates to observability\n49\t3. **Crash recovery** — state persisted after each task, engine resumes from last checkpoint\n50\t4. **Evaluator isolation** — separate workspace, `disallowedTools` enforcement, `source_access: false`\n51\t\n52\t## Starter Template Evaluation\n53\t\n54\t### Primary Technology Domain\n55\t\n56\tCLI developer tool — Node.js/TypeScript. Brownfield project with established toolchain.\n57\t\n58\t### Starter Options: Not Applicable (Brownfield)\n59\t\n60\tExisting project toolchain is retained:\n61\t\n62\t| Decision | Current (Keep) | Source |\n63\t|----------|---------------|--------|\n64\t| Language | TypeScript (strict) | Existing project |\n65\t| Build | tsup | Existing project |\n66\t| Test | vitest (unit) + BATS (integration) | Existing project |\n67\t| CLI | commander | Existing project |\n68\t| YAML | yaml package | Existing project |\n69\t| **New** | @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk | Research — replaces bash spawn |\n70\t\n71\t**No starter template needed.** One new dependency added. Internals reworked.\n72\t\n73\t## Core Architectural Decisions\n74\t\n75\t### Decision Priority Analysis\n76\t\n77\t**Critical Decisions (Block Implementation):**\n78\t1. Module boundaries — what code goes where\n79\t2. Evaluator workspace isolation — how to enforce source-free verification\n80\t3. Evaluator verdict schema — the contract between evaluator and engine\n81\t\n82\t**Important Decisions (Shape Architecture):**\n83\t4. Embedded template storage — where agent/workflow YAML files live in the package\n84\t5. Config resolution caching — resolve once or every dispatch\n85\t\n86\t**Deferred Decisions (Post-MVP):**\n87\t- PersonaNexus trait compilation algorithm (Growth phase)\n88\t- Pluggable evaluator strategies interface (Growth phase)\n89\t- Workflow marketplace format/registry (Vision phase)\n90\t\n91\t### AD1: Module Boundaries\n92\t\n93\t| Module | Responsibility | Key FRs |\n94\t|--------|---------------|---------|\n95\t| `workflow-parser` | Parse YAML, validate against JSON schema, resolve patches (embedded→user→project) | FR1-6, FR13-15 |\n96\t| `agent-resolver` | Resolve agent config through patch chain, compile to SDK inline subagent definition | FR7-12 |\n97\t| `workflow-engine` | Execute flow steps, manage iterations, handle `loop:` blocks, inject evaluator findings into retries | FR16-18, FR29-31 |\n98\t| `agent-dispatch` | Call Agent SDK `query()`, manage sessions (fresh/continue), inject trace IDs | FR19-23 |\n99\t| `evaluator` | Blind evaluator workspace setup, spawn, JSON verdict parsing | FR24-28 |\n100\t| `circuit-breaker` | Score-based stagnation detection, score history tracking | FR32-35 |\n101\t| `workflow-state` | Read/write workflow-state.yaml, crash recovery (resume from last completed task) | NFR6-8 |\n102\t\n103\t**Rationale:** 7 modules, each 100-200 LOC. Feedback loop (FR29-30) is part of `workflow-engine` — it's loop logic, not a separate concern. CLI commands (`init`, `run`, `validate`, `status`) are thin wrappers calling these modules. Observability (FR36-37) is a cross-cutting concern handled by trace ID injection in `agent-dispatch`, not a separate module.\n104\t\n105\t### AD2: Evaluator Workspace Isolation\n106\t\n107\t**Decision:** Temp directory with only story files + Docker access.\n108\t\n109\t```\n110\t/tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}/\n111\t  story-files/     # copied ACs from sprint\n112\t  verdict/         # evaluator writes JSON verdict here\n113\t```\n114\t\n115\tEngine copies story files to temp dir, spawns evaluator with `cwd` set to this directory. Agent SDK options enforce isolation:\n116\t- `bare: true` — no plugins, hooks, MCP, memory\n117\t- `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]` — read-only + execute only\n118\t- `cwd: /tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}` — no source code present\n119\t\n120\t**Rationale:** Simplest approach. Source isn't there because we never put it there. No git worktree complexity, no Docker-in-Docker. The Agent SDK's `cwd` + `disallowedTools` provide sufficient isolation.\n121\t\n122\t### AD3: Embedded Template Storage\n123\t\n124\t**Decision:** `templates/` directory in the npm package.\n125\t\n126\t```\n127\ttemplates/\n128\t  agents/\n129\t    dev.yaml\n130\t    qa.yaml\n131\t    architect.yaml\n132\t    pm.yaml\n133\t    sm.yaml\n134\t    analyst.yaml\n135\t    ux-designer.yaml\n136\t    tech-writer.yaml\n137\t    evaluator.yaml\n138\t  workflows/\n139\t    default.yaml\n140\t```\n141\t\n142\tIncluded via `package.json` `files` array. Readable, editable for debugging, consistent with existing pattern (`templates/Dockerfile.verify`).\n143\t\n144\t**Rationale:** Files over compiled strings. Easier to inspect, diff, and debug. The `codeharness init` command copies the default workflow to the project; embedded agents are resolved at runtime from the package location.\n145\t\n146\t### AD4: Config Resolution Caching\n147\t\n148\t**Decision:** Resolve all configs once at engine startup, cache in memory.\n149\t\n150\tOn `codeharness run`:\n151\t1. Resolve workflow: load embedded → apply user patch → apply project patch → cache\n152\t2. Resolve all referenced agents: same resolution chain → cache\n153\t3. Run engine with cached configs — no file I/O during execution\n154\t\n155\t**Rationale:** Config files don't change during a run. Caching guarantees NFR2 (<200ms resolution) and eliminates repeated file system reads during long-running execution.\n156\t\n157\t### AD5: Evaluator Verdict Schema\n158\t\n159\t**Decision:** Structured JSON enforced by Agent SDK `jsonSchema` option.\n160\t\n161\t```typescript\n162\tinterface EvaluatorVerdict {\n163\t  verdict: 'pass' | 'fail';\n164\t  score: {\n165\t    passed: number;\n166\t    failed: number;\n167\t    unknown: number;\n168\t    total: number;\n169\t  };\n170\t  findings: Array<{\n171\t    ac: number;\n172\t    description: string;\n173\t    status: 'pass' | 'fail' | 'unknown';\n174\t    evidence: {\n175\t      commands_run: string[];\n176\t      output_observed: string;\n177\t      reasoning: string;\n178\t    };\n179\t  }>;\n180\t  evaluator_trace_id: string;\n181\t  duration_seconds: number;\n182\t}\n183\t```\n184\t\n185\t**Rationale:** Replaces the 175-line proof document regex parser entirely. The Agent SDK validates the output against this schema — if the evaluator doesn't produce valid JSON, the SDK rejects it. Every AC verdict requires evidence (commands + output), enforcing the anti-leniency principle structurally.\n186\t\n187\t### Decision Impact Analysis\n188\t\n189\t**Implementation Sequence:**\n190\t1. `workflow-state` — foundation for crash recovery, needed by everything\n191\t2. `workflow-parser` — parse YAML + resolve patches, needed before execution\n192\t3. `agent-resolver` — resolve agent configs, needed before dispatch\n193\t4. `agent-dispatch` — SDK integration, needed before engine can run\n194\t5. `workflow-engine` — orchestrates everything above\n195\t6. `evaluator` — depends on dispatch + state\n196\t7. `circuit-breaker` — depends on evaluator verdicts\n197\t\n198\t**Cross-Component Dependencies:**\n199\t- `workflow-engine` depends on all other modules\n200\t- `evaluator` depends on `agent-dispatch` (for SDK spawn) and `workflow-state` (for verdict recording)\n201\t- `circuit-breaker` depends on `workflow-state` (reads score history)\n202\t- `agent-dispatch` depends on `agent-resolver` (for compiled subagent definitions)\n203\t\n204\t## Implementation Patterns & Consistency Rules\n205\t\n206\t### Naming Patterns\n207\t\n208\t**File naming:** `kebab-case.ts` for all source files. Already established (`workflow-parser.ts`, `agent-dispatch.ts`).\n209\t\n210\t**Export naming:** `camelCase` for functions, `PascalCase` for types/interfaces, `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for constants.\n211\t\n212\t**YAML keys:** `snake_case` for all workflow and agent config keys (`source_access`, `max_budget_usd`).\n213\t\n214\t**Patch files:** Named `{base-name}.patch.yaml`. Always. Not `.override.yaml` or `.custom.yaml`.\n215\t\n216\t### Structure Patterns\n217\t\n218\tEach module in `src/lib/` is one file with co-located test:\n219\t```\n220\tsrc/lib/workflow-parser.ts\n221\tsrc/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts\n222\t```\n223\t\n224\tEmbedded templates: `templates/agents/`, `templates/workflows/`.\n225\tUser-level: `~/.codeharness/agents/`, `~/.codeharness/workflows/`.\n226\tProject-level: `.codeharness/agents/`, `.codeharness/workflows/`.\n227\tNo alternative locations.\n228\t\n229\t### Format Patterns\n230\t\n231\t**Evaluator verdict:** JSON schema enforced (AD5). No alternative formats. Every AC requires `status`, `evidence.commands_run`, `evidence.output_observed`.\n232\t\n233\t**Workflow state:** YAML in `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml`. No JSON, no SQLite, no binary.\n234\t\n235\t**Resolved configs:** In-memory only. Never written to disk.\n236\t\n237\t### Error Handling Patterns\n238\t\n239\t| Failure | Response |\n240\t|---------|----------|\n241\t| API limit | Record in state, wait and retry |\n242\t| Network failure | Record in state, retry with backoff |\n243\t| Agent timeout | Score as UNKNOWN, continue |\n244\t| Binary not found | Fatal error, halt engine |\n245\t| Missing embedded agent | Fatal error at startup |\n246\t| Malformed patch YAML | Fatal error with parse error |\n247\t| Missing user/project patch | Silently skip |\n248\t| Evaluator timeout | All UNKNOWN, counts as scored iteration |\n249\t| Invalid evaluator JSON | Retry once, then all UNKNOWN |\n250\t| Docker not running | All UNKNOWN with \"Docker not available\" finding |\n251\t\n252\t### Process Patterns\n253\t\n254\t**State writes:** After EVERY task completion. Never batch. Never defer. Crash recovery guarantee.\n255\t\n256\t**Trace ID format:** `ch-{runId}-{iteration}-{taskName}` — deterministic, greppable. Example: `ch-abc123-3-verify`.\n257\t\n258\t**Session boundary enforcement:** `session: fresh` = new Agent SDK query with no resume/continue. No session reuse optimization across tasks.\n259\t\n260\t### Enforcement Guidelines\n261\t\n262\t**All agents implementing codeharness v2 MUST:**\n263\t- Run `vitest run` before marking any module complete — 80%+ coverage\n264\t- Use Agent SDK `query()` for all agent dispatch — never `execFileSync`\n265\t- Write workflow-state.yaml after every task — never hold state only in memory\n266\t- Use `bare: true` for all programmatic agent spawns\n267\t\n268\t**Anti-Patterns:**\n269\t- Caching evaluator verdicts across iterations (each is full re-verification)\n270\t- Writing resolved configs to disk (memory-only)\n271\t- Using `child_process.spawn` for Claude CLI\n272\t- Adding shell scripts to the execution path\n273\t\n274\t## Project Structure & Boundaries\n275\t\n276\t### Complete Project Directory Structure\n277\t\n278\t```\n279\tcodeharness/\n280\t├── package.json\n281\t├── tsconfig.json\n282\t├── tsup.config.ts\n283\t├── vitest.config.ts\n284\t├── .github/workflows/release.yml\n285\t│\n286\t├── src/\n287\t│   ├── index.ts                           # CLI entry point (commander)\n288\t│   │\n289\t│   ├── commands/                           # CLI command handlers\n290\t│   │   ├── init.ts                        # REWORK — add workflow generation, strip beads\n291\t│   │   ├── run.ts                         # REWORK — use workflow-engine instead of Ralph\n292\t│   │   ├── validate.ts                    # NEW — schema validation command\n293\t│   │   ├── status.ts                      # REWORK — show workflow-state, strip beads\n294\t│   │   ├── verify.ts                      # REWORK — becomes evaluator trigger only\n295\t│   │   ├── coverage.ts                    # KEEP as-is\n296\t│   │   ├── doc-health.ts                  # KEEP as-is\n297\t│   │   ├── stack.ts                       # KEEP as-is\n298\t│   │   ├── query.ts                       # KEEP as-is (observability queries)\n299\t│   │   ├── bridge.ts                      # REWORK — strip beads, keep BMAD bridge\n300\t│   │   ├── sync.ts                        # REWORK — strip beads sync\n301\t│   │   ├── onboard.ts                     # REWORK — strip beads calls\n302\t│   │   ├── teardown.ts                    # REWORK — update for new file layout\n303\t│   │   ├── state.ts                       # REWORK — point at workflow-state.yaml\n304\t│   │   ├── retro-import.ts               # REWORK — strip beads imports\n305\t│   │   ├── github-import.ts              # REWORK — strip beads imports\n306\t│   │   ├── verify-env.ts                  # REWORK — evolve into evaluator setup\n307\t│   │   └── __tests__/\n308\t│   │\n309\t│   ├── lib/                               # Core modules\n310\t│   │   │\n311\t│   │   │  # ── NEW MODULES (v2 architecture) ──\n312\t│   │   ├── workflow-parser.ts             # YAML parse, schema validate, patch resolution\n313\t│   │   ├── agent-resolver.ts             # Agent config resolution, SDK compilation\n314\t│   │   ├── workflow-engine.ts            # Flow execution, loops, finding injection\n315\t│   │   ├── agent-dispatch.ts             # Agent SDK query(), sessions, trace IDs\n316\t│   │   ├── evaluator.ts                  # Blind evaluator workspace + spawn + verdict parsing\n317\t│   │   ├── circuit-breaker.ts            # Score-based stagnation detection (TS rewrite)\n318\t│   │   ├── workflow-state.ts             # State persistence, crash recovery (replaces state.ts)\n319\t│   │   │\n320\t│   │   │  # ── KEPT MODULES (existing, no changes) ──\n321\t│   │   ├── output.ts                      # Console output utilities\n322\t│   │   ├── stack-detect.ts               # Stack detection for init\n323\t│   │   ├── stack-path.ts                 # Docker compose and OTLP config paths\n324\t│   │   ├── docker.ts                      # Docker Compose lifecycle management\n325\t│   │   ├── otlp.ts                        # OpenTelemetry instrumentation setup\n326\t│   │   ├── scanner.ts                     # Codebase scanning\n327\t│   │   ├── scan-cache.ts                 # Scan result persistence\n328\t│   │   ├── coverage.ts                    # Coverage tool detection\n329\t│   │   ├── doc-health.ts                 # Documentation freshness checking\n330\t│   │   ├── templates.ts                   # File rendering and generation\n331\t│   │   ├── github.ts                      # GitHub CLI wrapper\n332\t│   │   ├── retro-parser.ts              # Retrospective markdown parsing\n333\t│   │   │\n334\t│   │   │  # ── REWORK MODULES (strip beads, keep core logic) ──\n335\t│   │   ├── bmad.ts                        # REWORK — strip beads gap-IDs, keep BMAD install/patch\n336\t│   │   ├── epic-generator.ts             # REWORK — strip beads gap-IDs, keep epic generation\n337\t│   │   ├── onboard-checks.ts            # REWORK — strip beads calls, keep preconditions\n338\t│   │   ├── deps.ts                        # REWORK — remove showboat/beads deps\n339\t│   │   ├── verify-env.ts                 # REWORK — evolve into evaluator workspace setup\n340\t│   │   │\n341\t│   │   └── __tests__/                     # Co-located unit tests (update with source)\n342\t│   │\n343\t│   ├── templates/                         # Code-generated templates\n344\t│   │   ├── readme.ts                      # KEEP — README generator\n345\t│   │   ├── docker-compose.ts             # KEEP — observability stack template\n346\t│   │   ├── otel-config.ts               # KEEP — OpenTelemetry config\n347\t│   │   ├── bmad-patches.ts              # KEEP — BMAD workflow patch templates\n348\t│   │   └── __tests__/\n349\t│   │\n350\t│   └── schemas/                           # JSON schemas (NEW)\n351\t│       ├── workflow.schema.json\n352\t│       ├── agent.schema.json\n353\t│       └── verdict.schema.json\n354\t│\n355\t├── templates/                             # Embedded defaults (shipped in npm)\n356\t│   ├── agents/                            # 9 agent YAMLs (8 BMAD + evaluator)\n357\t│   │   ├── dev.yaml\n358\t│   │   ├── qa.yaml\n359\t│   │   ├── architect.yaml\n360\t│   │   ├── pm.yaml\n361\t│   │   ├── sm.yaml\n362\t│   │   ├── analyst.yaml\n363\t│   │   ├── ux-designer.yaml\n364\t│   │   ├── tech-writer.yaml\n365\t│   │   └── evaluator.yaml\n366\t│   └── workflows/\n367\t│       └── default.yaml                   # Default sprint execution workflow\n368\t│\n369\t├── tests/                                 # BATS integration tests (rework for v2)\n370\t│\n371\t├── .claude-plugin/\n372\t│   └── plugin.json                        # REWORK — update hooks, remove old references\n373\t│\n374\t├── skills/                                # REWORK — update for v2 architecture\n375\t│   ├── harness-run/\n376\t│   ├── harness-status/\n377\t│   └── harness-init/\n378\t│\n379\t└── dist/                                  # Build output (tsup)\n380\t```\n381\t\n382\t### Complete File Migration Plan\n383\t\n384\t#### DELETE (40+ files)\n385\t\n386\t**Entire directories:**\n387\t- `ralph/` — 23 files (ralph.sh, drivers/, lib/, logs/, state files)\n388\t- `hooks/` — 5 files (4 bash hooks + hooks.json)\n389\t\n390\t**From `src/lib/` (7 files):**\n391\t- `beads.ts` — Beads CLI wrapper (entire beads integration removed)\n392\t- `beads-sync.ts` — Beads ↔ story sync\n393\t- `verify.ts` — 175-line proof parser (replaced by evaluator.ts)\n394\t- `verify-parser.ts` — Story AC parser (simplified into evaluator)\n395\t- `verifier-session.ts` — Black-box verifier subprocess (evolved into evaluator.ts)\n396\t- `patch-engine.ts` — Marker-based patching (replaced by workflow-parser.ts)\n397\t- `retry-state.ts` — Retry counter persistence (merged into workflow-state.ts)\n398\t- `state.ts` — Old session flags state (replaced by workflow-state.ts)\n399\t\n400\t**From `src/templates/` (3 files):**\n401\t- `showboat-template.ts` — Proof document format (replaced by JSON verdict)\n402\t- `verify-prompt.ts` — Black-box verifier prompt (replaced by evaluator agent YAML)\n403\t- `ralph-prompt.ts` — Ralph loop prompt (replaced by workflow engine)\n404\t\n405\t**From `src/commands/` (1 file):**\n406\t- `retry.ts` — Retry command (merged into workflow-state)\n407\t\n408\t**All corresponding test files for deleted sources.**\n409\t\n410\t#### REWORK — Beads Cleanup (12 files)\n411\t\n412\tThese files import beads functions that must be surgically removed:\n413\t\n414\t| File | What to Remove | What to Keep |\n415\t|------|---------------|-------------|\n416\t| `src/lib/bmad.ts` | `appendGapId`, beads issue creation | BMAD install, workflow patching |\n417\t| `src/lib/epic-generator.ts` | `appendGapId`, beads calls | Epic generation from scan |\n418\t| `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` | Beads precondition checks | Non-beads preconditions |\n419\t| `src/lib/deps.ts` | Showboat/beads dep installation | Claude, Docker dep checks |\n420\t| `src/lib/verify-env.ts` | Old verifier workspace logic | Evolve into evaluator workspace |\n421\t| `src/commands/bridge.ts` | `createIssue`, `listIssues` imports | BMAD story bridge logic |\n422\t| `src/commands/init.ts` | Beads init, hook installation | Stack detect, workflow generation |\n423\t| `src/commands/onboard.ts` | Beads calls from epic-generator | Scanning, epic generation |\n424\t| `src/commands/status.ts` | Beads status display | Workflow-state display |\n425\t| `src/commands/sync.ts` | Beads sync operations | Sprint-status sync |\n426\t| `src/commands/teardown.ts` | Old patch-engine calls | New file layout cleanup |\n427\t| `src/commands/verify.ts` | Self-verification, proof parsing | Evaluator trigger only |\n428\t\n429\t#### REWORK — Architecture Changes (5 files)\n430\t\n431\t| File | Change |\n432\t|------|--------|\n433\t| `src/commands/run.ts` | Replace Ralph spawn with workflow-engine call |\n434\t| `src/commands/state.ts` | Point at workflow-state.yaml instead of old state |\n435\t| `src/commands/retro-import.ts` | Strip beads imports |\n436\t| `src/commands/github-import.ts` | Strip beads imports |\n437\t| `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` | Remove old hook references, update version |\n438\t\n439\t#### REWORK — Skills (3 directories)\n440\t\n441\t| Skill | Change |\n442\t|-------|--------|\n443\t| `skills/harness-run/` | Update to reference workflow-engine |\n444\t| `skills/harness-status/` | Update to reference workflow-state |\n445\t| `skills/harness-init/` | Update for new init flow |\n446\t\n447\t#### NEW (20+ files)\n448\t\n449\t- 7 core modules in `src/lib/` (workflow-parser, agent-resolver, workflow-engine, agent-dispatch, evaluator, circuit-breaker, workflow-state)\n450\t- 3 JSON schemas in `src/schemas/`\n451\t- 9 agent YAMLs in `templates/agents/`\n452\t- 1 workflow YAML in `templates/workflows/`\n453\t- 1 new command (`src/commands/validate.ts`)\n454\t- Co-located tests for all new modules\n455\t\n456\t### FR → Module Mapping\n457\t\n458\t| FR Group | Module |\n459\t|----------|--------|\n460\t| FR1-6, FR13-15 (Workflow + Config) | workflow-parser |\n461\t| FR7-12 (Agent Config) | agent-resolver |\n462\t| FR16-18, FR29-31 (Execution + Feedback) | workflow-engine |\n463\t| FR19-23 (Dispatch) | agent-dispatch |\n464\t| FR24-28 (Verification) | evaluator |\n465\t| FR32-35 (Circuit Breaker) | circuit-breaker |\n466\t| FR36-37 (Observability) | agent-dispatch (trace IDs) |\n467\t| FR38-41 (CLI) | commands/*.ts |\n468\t\n469\t### Dependency Chain Breaks to Handle\n470\t\n471\t| Deleted Module | Dependents That Need Cleanup |\n472\t|---------------|------------------------------|\n473\t| `beads.ts` | bmad.ts, epic-generator.ts, onboard-checks.ts, bridge, github-import, init, onboard, retro-import, status, sync, verify |\n474\t| `beads-sync.ts` | sync.ts, verify.ts, run.ts |\n475\t| `verify-parser.ts` | verify.ts |\n476\t| `verifier-session.ts` | (no external dependents — self-contained) |\n477\t| `patch-engine.ts` | bmad.ts, teardown.ts |\n478\t| `retry-state.ts` | retry.ts (deleted), run.ts |\n479\t| `state.ts` | verify.ts, status.ts, state.ts command, init.ts |\n480\t| `ralph-prompt.ts` | run.ts |\n481\t| `showboat-template.ts` | verify.ts |\n482\t\n483\t### Integration Boundaries & Data Flow\n484\t\n485\t```\n486\tcodeharness run\n487\t  → workflow-parser: load + resolve workflow YAML\n488\t  → agent-resolver: resolve all referenced agents, cache\n489\t  → workflow-engine: execute flow steps\n490\t    → per-story tasks:\n491\t        agent-dispatch: SDK query() → agent works → returns\n492\t        workflow-state: write checkpoint\n493\t    → per-run tasks (verify):\n494\t        evaluator: setup workspace → agent-dispatch → parse verdict\n495\t        workflow-state: write checkpoint + scores\n496\t        circuit-breaker: evaluate stagnation\n497\t    → loop block: repeat with findings injected\n498\t  → workflow-state: write final status\n499\t```\n500\t\n501\t## Architecture Validation Results\n502\t\n503\t### Coherence Validation\n504\t\n505\t**Decision Compatibility:** All technology choices (Agent SDK + TypeScript + commander + yaml) are Node.js ecosystem, no conflicts. Agent SDK async generator + sequential engine execution are compatible. JSON schema validation consistent across workflow, agent, and verdict schemas.\n506\t\n507\t**Pattern Consistency:** kebab-case files + camelCase exports matches existing codebase. snake_case YAML keys is standard cross-language convention. Write-after-task state pattern aligns with crash recovery requirement.\n508\t\n509\t**Structure Alignment:** 7 modules in `src/lib/` with co-located tests matches existing structure. Templates in `templates/` matches existing distribution. `.codeharness/` for project config is clean separation from `.claude/`.\n510\t\n511\t**No contradictions found.**\n512\t\n513\t### Requirements Coverage\n514\t\n515\t**43 FRs:** All mapped to specific modules. No FR unaddressed.\n516\t\n517\t**18 NFRs:** All addressed — performance by caching, reliability by state persistence, integration by Agent SDK, code quality by project structure.\n518\t\n519\t**Minor gap:** Verdict schema needs `infrastructure_available: boolean` for graceful degradation when Docker is unavailable (Journey 5). Resolution: add the field.\n520\t\n521\t### Implementation Readiness\n522\t\n523\t- 5 architectural decisions documented with rationale\n524\t- Implementation sequence defined (state → parser → resolver → dispatch → engine → evaluator → circuit-breaker)\n525\t- Full directory tree with every file specified\n526\t- Legacy deletion targets listed explicitly\n527\t- Error handling patterns cover all failure modes\n528\t- Enforcement guidelines and anti-patterns documented\n529\t\n530\t### Architecture Completeness Checklist\n531\t\n532\t- [x] Project context analyzed\n533\t- [x] Technical constraints identified\n534\t- [x] Cross-cutting concerns mapped (config resolution, trace IDs, crash recovery, evaluator isolation)\n535\t- [x] 5 core architectural decisions documented\n536\t- [x] Technology stack specified\n537\t- [x] Naming, structure, format, error, and process patterns defined\n538\t- [x] Complete directory structure with every file classified (DELETE/REWORK/KEEP/NEW)\n539\t- [x] FR→module mapping complete\n540\t- [x] Integration boundaries and data flow documented\n541\t- [x] Beads dependency chain mapped — 12 files need surgical cleanup\n542\t- [x] All 17 existing commands accounted for (not just the 4 new/reworked ones)\n543\t- [x] All 14 kept lib modules listed with their role in v2\n544\t- [x] All 4 kept templates listed\n545\t- [x] Skills and plugin.json rework noted\n546\t- [x] Dependency chain breaks documented with specific cleanup actions\n547\t\n548\t### Architecture Readiness Assessment\n549\t\n550\t**Status:** READY FOR IMPLEMENTATION\n551\t**Confidence:** High\n552\t\n553\t**Migration scope (revised):**\n554\t- ~40 files deleted (ralph/, hooks/, 8 lib modules, 3 templates, 1 command + tests)\n555\t- ~17 files reworked (12 beads cleanup, 5 architecture changes)\n556\t- ~14 lib files kept as-is\n557\t- ~20 new files (7 modules, 3 schemas, 10 templates, tests)\n558\t\n559\t**Strengths:** Clean module boundaries, complete file migration plan, dependency chain breaks documented, official SDK replaces bash spawning, beads-level state simplicity, structural evaluator isolation.\n560\t\n561\t**Key risk:** Beads cleanup touches 12 files — must be done atomically to avoid broken imports. Recommended: delete beads.ts + beads-sync.ts first, then fix all compiler errors in one pass.\n562\t\n563\t### AD6: Issue Tracking (Beads Replacement)\n564\t\n565\t**Problem:** Beads is removed but the underlying need remains — retro findings, bugs, and tech debt need a path from \"discovered\" to \"scheduled\" to \"implemented.\" BMAD handles planned stories well but not unplanned issues.\n566\t\n567\t**Decision:** Simple `issues.yaml` file parallel to `sprint-status.yaml`.\n568\t\n569\t```yaml\n570\t# .codeharness/issues.yaml (or _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/issues.yaml)\n571\tissues:\n572\t  - id: issue-001\n573\t    title: Docker timeout handling too aggressive\n574\t    source: retro-epic-15       # where it came from\n575\t    priority: high\n576\t    status: ready-for-dev       # same statuses as stories\n577\t  - id: issue-002\n578\t    title: Evaluator too lenient on API error codes\n579\t    source: manual\n580\t    priority: medium\n581\t    status: backlog\n582\t```\n583\t\n584\t**How it works:**\n585\t- `codeharness issue create \"title\" --priority high --source retro-epic-15` → adds to issues.yaml\n586\t- Retro workflow tags findings as `actionable: true` → auto-added to issues.yaml\n587\t- Workflow engine reads both `sprint-status.yaml` (stories) AND `issues.yaml` (issues)\n588\t- Issues interleaved into execution based on priority\n589\t- Same statuses, same execution path, same verification — the engine doesn't distinguish stories from issues\n590\t\n591\t**Rationale:** File-based, no external dependencies, beads-level simplicity. Everything goes through the workflow engine. No separate issue tracker to maintain. Retro findings get a mechanical path to implementation instead of rotting in markdown.\n592\t\n593\t**Implementation Priority:**\n594\t1. Beads cleanup (unblock everything — 12 files, surgical removal)\n595\t2. Legacy deletion (ralph/, hooks/, old verify/proof modules)\n596\t3. New modules in dependency order (state → parser → resolver → dispatch → engine → evaluator → circuit-breaker)\n597\t4. Command rework (run.ts, verify.ts, init.ts, status.ts)\n598\t5. Skills and plugin.json update\n599\t6. Integration tests\n600\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XScTPWbxkcynzQq2rGASAG","session_id":"c54cfa66-957c-4f2c-a205-da1113d93a9b","uuid":"80ccba60-df73-4ac6-8bae-fa92808c4ef3","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:03:21.991Z"}
