{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R2QTCJBNP2wjAc3xBM2nFR","type":"tool_result","content":"36:2. **A single adversarial verification pass** against the final built artifact. No per-story micro-verification. No session flags. No proof document regex parsing. One blind evaluator agent — no source code access, only Docker, observability, and documentation — exercises the final artifact subjectively and produces a structured JSON verdict. The evaluator reads ACs in user language and independently figures out how to test them.\n48:- **Aggressive legacy removal.** The 4-format proof parser, session flags, self-verification path, per-story hooks, and hardcoded Ralph logic all get deleted. Only clean code survives.\n100:2. Flow execution engine (sequential steps, `loop:` blocks, task scope resolution)\n133:**Legacy removal scope:** Deleting Ralph, hooks, and verification paths simultaneously is a big bang. **Mitigation:** Build the new engine alongside the old code. Switch over when the new engine passes the same test suite. Then delete.\n163:  tasks:\n168:  flow:\n173:      - loop:\n234:1. For each `per-story` task in flow order: resolve agent config (embedded → user → project patches) → compile to SDK inline subagent → generate trace ID → spawn session (fresh or continue) → pass input contract → collect output\n235:2. For each `per-run` task: spawn evaluator with all story ACs, trace IDs, observability endpoints → collect structured JSON verdict + findings\n260:- `flow` — ordered execution steps with `loop:` blocks for feedback loops\n261:- Task properties: `scope` (per-story/per-run), `session` (fresh/continue), `source_access` (boolean), `agent` (agent name)\n330:- FR2: User can specify per-task properties: agent assignment, scope (per-story/per-run), session boundary (fresh/continue), source access, input/output contracts, and prompt template\n332:- FR4: User can define loop steps in the flow using a `loop:` block containing an ordered list of tasks to repeat\n354:- FR17: System executes `per-story` tasks once for each story in the sprint\n355:- FR18: System executes `per-run` tasks once after all stories in the current phase complete\n360:- FR23: System enforces `source_access: false` by spawning the agent in a workspace with no source code"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XScTPWbxkcynzQq2rGASAG","session_id":"c54cfa66-957c-4f2c-a205-da1113d93a9b","uuid":"70eb7a10-6754-4972-87f4-222e27a6370f","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:03:48.788Z"}
