{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PEuYL69tiDERohezH4r6YC","type":"tool_result","content":"155\t### Journey 3: Agent & Workflow Customization\n156\t\n157\tNew project — React frontend. Alex patches the default workflow and the dev agent at project level:\n158\t\n159\t```yaml\n160\t# .codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml\n161\textends: embedded://default\n162\toverrides:\n163\t  tasks:\n164\t    implement:\n165\t      model: opus\n166\t    verify:\n167\t      maxBudgetUsd: 10\n168\t  flow:\n169\t    replace:\n170\t      - implement\n171\t      - build\n172\t      - verify\n173\t      - loop:\n174\t        - retry\n175\t        - build\n176\t        - verify\n177\t```\n178\t\n179\t```yaml\n180\t# .codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml\n181\textends: embedded://dev\n182\toverrides:\n183\t  personality:\n184\t    traits:\n185\t      rigor: 0.9\n186\tprompt_patches:\n187\t  append: |\n188\t    This project uses React + Vite. Run npm run build before\n189\t    considering implementation complete.\n190\t```\n191\t\n192\tNo TypeScript changes, no bash editing. Patches override specific fields; everything else inherits from the embedded defaults.\n193\t\n194\t### Journey 4: Broken Environment\n195\t\n196\tAlex runs `codeharness init` on a machine without Docker installed. The CLI detects the missing dependency and reports: \"Docker not found — required for blind evaluator verification. Install Docker Desktop and re-run init.\"\n197\t\n198\tAlex installs Docker but has no BMAD project set up. `codeharness init` reports: \"No BMAD agent configs found at `_bmad/bmm/agents/`. Run BMAD setup first, or use `--skip-bmad` to use only embedded agents.\"\n199\t\n200\tAlex uses `--skip-bmad`. Init succeeds with embedded agents only. Later, `codeharness run` completes stories but the evaluator fails — Docker daemon isn't running. Engine reports: \"Evaluator spawn failed: Docker daemon not running. Verdict: UNKNOWN for all ACs. Start Docker and resume with `codeharness run --resume`.\"\n201\t\n202\tAlex starts Docker, runs `--resume`. Engine picks up from the verify step, evaluator exercises the artifact. Done.\n203\t\n204\t### Journey 5: Retro Findings → Issues → Implementation"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XScTPWbxkcynzQq2rGASAG","session_id":"c54cfa66-957c-4f2c-a205-da1113d93a9b","uuid":"b8120470-298f-43e2-ba9d-9741985f12f2","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:03:53.711Z"}
