{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JDHxzhCjg1KhRG9h8vqkWM","type":"tool_result","content":"225\t\n226\tIn the next sprint, `codeharness run` picks up issue-003 (high priority, ready-for-dev) alongside the planned stories. The dev agent gets the issue description as context, fixes the timeout handling, commits. The evaluator re-verifies the full artifact including the fix.\n227\t\n228\tAlex also runs `codeharness issue create \"Add rate limiter to /api/users\" --priority medium` to manually log a bug found during demo. It appears in `issues.yaml` and will be picked up in a future sprint based on priority.\n229\t\n230\t### Journey 6: Engine Execution Flow\n231\t\n232\tEngine reads workflow YAML (resolved through embedded → user → project patches) and sprint-status.yaml:\n233\t\n234\t1. For each `per-story` task in flow order: resolve agent config (embedded → user → project patches) → compile to SDK inline subagent → generate trace ID → spawn session (fresh or continue) → pass input contract → collect output\n235\t2. For each `per-run` task: spawn evaluator with all story ACs, trace IDs, observability endpoints → collect structured JSON verdict + findings\n236\t3. On loop step: filter to failed stories → spawn dev with findings injected → rebuild → re-verify entire artifact\n237\t4. Terminate on: all ACs pass OR circuit breaker (score stagnation) OR max iterations\n238\t\n239\t## Developer Tool Requirements\n240\t\n241\t### Technical Architecture\n242\t\n243\t**Runtime:** Node.js (TypeScript). Single runtime, no multi-platform builds.\n244\t\n245\t**Dependencies:** `commander`, `yaml`, `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` (new — replaces bash `spawn`).\n246\t\n247\t**Distribution:** npm registry (CLI binary) + Claude Code plugin registry (skills, hooks, commands). No additional channels.\n248\t\n249\t**IDE Integration:** None. Rides on Claude Code's VS Code/JetBrains extensions.\n250\t\n251\t### API Surface — Workflow YAML Schema\n252\t\n253\tThe workflow YAML is the primary API surface:\n254\t- Formally specified with a JSON schema\n255\t- Validatable via `codeharness validate`\n256\t- Self-documenting — the default workflow is the best documentation\n257\t\n258\tKey schema elements:\n259\t- `tasks` — named task definitions with agent, scope, session, input/output, prompt\n260\t- `flow` — ordered execution steps with `loop:` blocks for feedback loops\n261\t- Task properties: `scope` (per-story/per-run), `session` (fresh/continue), `source_access` (boolean), `agent` (agent name)\n262\t\n263\t### Agent Configuration Format\n264\t\n265\tBMAD-compatible base fields (required) with optional PersonaNexus-compatible traits:\n266\t\n267\t```yaml\n268\tname: evaluator\n269\trole:\n270\t  title: Adversarial QA Evaluator\n271\t  purpose: Exercise the built artifact and determine if it actually works\n272\tpersona:\n273\t  identity: Senior QA who trusts nothing without evidence\n274\t  communication_style: Blunt, evidence-first"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XScTPWbxkcynzQq2rGASAG","session_id":"c54cfa66-957c-4f2c-a205-da1113d93a9b","uuid":"222af1ee-b2f5-4bd1-b580-b3caa2626e3a","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:03:56.807Z"}
