{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SoVRzWBEJZuP7t2aSHftfF","type":"tool_result","content":"133\t**Legacy removal scope:** Deleting Ralph, hooks, and verification paths simultaneously is a big bang. **Mitigation:** Build the new engine alongside the old code. Switch over when the new engine passes the same test suite. Then delete.\n134\t\n135\t**Solo developer:** One person doing engine + evaluator + config system + legacy removal + tests. **Mitigation:** The agents do the implementation work. Codeharness v2 is the first real test of codeharness v2.\n136\t\n137\t## User Journeys\n138\t\n139\t### Journey 1: First Run (Happy Path)\n140\t\n141\tAlex has a BMAD sprint plan with 8 stories for a Node.js API. Runs `codeharness init`, then `codeharness run`. No workflow YAML to write — the default handles it.\n142\t\n143\tThe dev agent implements each story in a fresh session. After all 8 complete, the blind evaluator spawns — no source access, only Docker, observability endpoints, and story ACs. It independently figures out how to exercise each AC — makes real HTTP requests, checks DB state, queries traces. Verdict: 7/8 pass. Finding for AC5: \"POST /users returns 201 but doesn't persist — `docker exec psql -c 'SELECT count(*) FROM users'` returns 0.\"\n144\t\n145\tThe engine feeds that finding into the dev agent's prompt for story 5 only. Dev fixes it, commits. Engine rebuilds, evaluator re-verifies the entire artifact from scratch. 8/8. Done.\n146\t\n147\t### Journey 2: Evaluator Rejection Loop\n148\t\n149\tEvaluator rejects three times. Scores: 4/8 → 5/8 → 5/8. Third iteration shows no score improvement — circuit breaker triggers on stagnation.\n150\t\n151\tAlex sees: \"Circuit breaker: evaluator score stuck at 5/8 across 2 iterations. Remaining failures: AC3 (WebSocket never connected), AC6 (rate limiter not enforced — 1000 requests all returned 200).\"\n152\t\n153\tAlex fixes AC3 manually, defers AC6 to next sprint, re-runs. Evaluator passes on the scoped ACs.\n154\t\n155\t### Journey 3: Agent & Workflow Customization\n156\t\n157\tNew project — React frontend. Alex patches the default workflow and the dev agent at project level:\n158\t\n159\t```yaml\n160\t# .codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml\n161\textends: embedded://default\n162\toverrides:"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XScTPWbxkcynzQq2rGASAG","session_id":"c54cfa66-957c-4f2c-a205-da1113d93a9b","uuid":"d41c165a-a693-4f2c-bae5-f05fbaa5163b","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:04:00.541Z"}
