{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Qi2hyWsUAHJDdecbkWvXAn","type":"tool_result","content":"131-**Evaluator quality:** Anthropic found that \"out of the box, Claude is a poor QA agent.\" The evaluator judges subjectively — it reads ACs and independently exercises the artifact, requiring evidence for every verdict. **Mitigation:** Structured JSON output forces evidence. Calibrate against known-broken artifacts. Log all evaluator sessions. Run multiple trials (pass^3 is the real metric). Iterate on the evaluator prompt across real projects.\n132-\n133:**Legacy removal scope:** Deleting Ralph, hooks, and verification paths simultaneously is a big bang. **Mitigation:** Build the new engine alongside the old code. Switch over when the new engine passes the same test suite. Then delete.\n134-\n135-**Solo developer:** One person doing engine + evaluator + config system + legacy removal + tests. **Mitigation:** The agents do the implementation work. Codeharness v2 is the first real test of codeharness v2.\n--\n161-extends: embedded://default\n162-overrides:\n163:  tasks:\n164:    implement:\n165-      model: opus\n166:    verify:\n167-      maxBudgetUsd: 10\n168-  flow:\n--\n358-- FR21: System passes defined input contracts to each task and collects defined outputs\n359-- FR22: System generates a unique trace ID per iteration and injects it into agent prompts\n360:- FR23: System enforces `source_access: false` by spawning the agent in a workspace with no source code\n361-\n362-### Adversarial Verification"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XScTPWbxkcynzQq2rGASAG","session_id":"c54cfa66-957c-4f2c-a205-da1113d93a9b","uuid":"92739370-3fc0-43ee-9858-107761417cc0","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:04:05.240Z"}
