{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UxrgGEUjHD8hxpE118tmNo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013ZFf88MoHS1vurdYqkJkdi","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-1-workflow-yaml-json-schema.md","old_string":"- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/schemas/` directory and `workflow.schema.json` (AC: #8)\n  - [ ] Create `src/schemas/` directory\n  - [ ] Define the JSON schema with `$schema`, `$id`, `type: object`, `required: [tasks, flow]`\n  - [ ] Define `tasks` as object with `additionalProperties` referencing a task definition schema\n  - [ ] Define task properties: `agent` (string, required), `scope` (enum: per-story, per-run), `session` (enum: fresh, continue), `source_access` (boolean), `prompt_template` (string), `input_contract` (object), `output_contract` (object), `max_budget_usd` (number)\n  - [ ] Define `flow` as an array of items that are either strings (task references) or objects with a `loop` key containing an array of strings\n  - [ ] Set sensible defaults: `scope: per-story`, `session: fresh`, `source_access: true`\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Create schema validation utility (AC: #1-7, #9)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` (or co-locate in workflow-parser as a standalone validate function)\n  - [ ] Use `ajv` for JSON schema validation — or use a zero-dependency approach: hand-written validate function since the schema is small and `ajv` adds ~150KB. Decision: use `ajv` (or `ajv/dist/2020`) for correctness and maintainability; it's a dev-time cost, not a runtime concern for a CLI tool\n  - [ ] Export `validateWorkflowYaml(data: unknown): ValidationResult` returning `{ valid: boolean; errors: ValidationError[] }`\n  - [ ] Each `ValidationError` includes `path` (JSON pointer), `message` (human-readable), `keyword` (schema keyword that failed)\n  - [ ] Load schema from `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` via `resolveJsonModule`\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate.test.ts` (or `src/schemas/__tests__/workflow-schema.test.ts`)\n  - [ ] Test: valid minimal workflow passes (tasks + flow)\n  - [ ] Test: valid full workflow with all optional fields passes\n  - [ ] Test: missing `tasks` field fails with specific error\n  - [ ] Test: missing `flow` field fails with specific error\n  - [ ] Test: invalid `scope` value fails with specific error\n  - [ ] Test: invalid `session` value fails with specific error\n  - [ ] Test: `loop:` block in flow is structurally valid\n  - [ ] Test: missing `agent` in task fails with specific error\n  - [ ] Test: optional fields accepted when present, pass when absent\n  - [ ] Test: `source_access` as non-boolean fails\n  - [ ] Test: `max_budget_usd` as non-number fails\n  - [ ] Test: empty `tasks` object is valid (degenerate but schema-legal)\n  - [ ] Test: empty `flow` array is valid (degenerate but schema-legal)\n  - [ ] Target 80%+ coverage on the validation module","new_string":"- [x] Task 1: Create `src/schemas/` directory and `workflow.schema.json` (AC: #8)\n  - [x] Create `src/schemas/` directory\n  - [x] Define the JSON schema with `$schema`, `$id`, `type: object`, `required: [tasks, flow]`\n  - [x] Define `tasks` as object with `additionalProperties` referencing a task definition schema\n  - [x] Define task properties: `agent` (string, required), `scope` (enum: per-story, per-run), `session` (enum: fresh, continue), `source_access` (boolean), `prompt_template` (string), `input_contract` (object), `output_contract` (object), `max_budget_usd` (number)\n  - [x] Define `flow` as an array of items that are either strings (task references) or objects with a `loop` key containing an array of strings\n  - [x] Set sensible defaults: `scope: per-story`, `session: fresh`, `source_access: true`\n\n- [x] Task 2: Create schema validation utility (AC: #1-7, #9)\n  - [x] Create `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` (or co-locate in workflow-parser as a standalone validate function)\n  - [x] Use `ajv` for JSON schema validation — or use a zero-dependency approach: hand-written validate function since the schema is small and `ajv` adds ~150KB. Decision: use `ajv` (or `ajv/dist/2020`) for correctness and maintainability; it's a dev-time cost, not a runtime concern for a CLI tool\n  - [x] Export `validateWorkflowYaml(data: unknown): ValidationResult` returning `{ valid: boolean; errors: ValidationError[] }`\n  - [x] Each `ValidationError` includes `path` (JSON pointer), `message` (human-readable), `keyword` (schema keyword that failed)\n  - [x] Load schema from `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` via `resolveJsonModule`\n\n- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate.test.ts` (or `src/schemas/__tests__/workflow-schema.test.ts`)\n  - [x] Test: valid minimal workflow passes (tasks + flow)\n  - [x] Test: valid full workflow with all optional fields passes\n  - [x] Test: missing `tasks` field fails with specific error\n  - [x] Test: missing `flow` field fails with specific error\n  - [x] Test: invalid `scope` value fails with specific error\n  - [x] Test: invalid `session` value fails with specific error\n  - [x] Test: `loop:` block in flow is structurally valid\n  - [x] Test: missing `agent` in task fails with specific error\n  - [x] Test: optional fields accepted when present, pass when absent\n  - [x] Test: `source_access` as non-boolean fails\n  - [x] Test: `max_budget_usd` as non-number fails\n  - [x] Test: empty `tasks` object is valid (degenerate but schema-legal)\n  - [x] Test: empty `flow` array is valid (degenerate but schema-legal)\n  - [x] Target 80%+ coverage on the validation module"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":211,"cache_read_input_tokens":32536,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2