{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T5izCnprn3BanMVUeAKGXz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\nImplementation complete. Here is what was done:\n\n**Files created:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` — JSON Schema (draft-07) defining valid workflow YAML structure with `tasks` (named task definitions requiring `agent`, optional `scope`/`session`/`source_access`/`prompt_template`/`input_contract`/`output_contract`/`max_budget_usd`) and `flow` (array of string task refs or `loop:` blocks).\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — Validation utility exporting `validateWorkflowSchema(data)` and `validateAgainstSchema(data, validator)` with `ValidationResult`/`ValidationError` interfaces.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate.test.ts` — 24 unit tests covering all 10 acceptance criteria plus edge cases.\n\n**Dependency added:** `ajv` (production dependency)\n\n**Results:** 24/24 tests pass. Full suite: 3576/3576 pass. Build succeeds. Lint clean (no new errors). Coverage on `schema-validate.ts`: 100% statements/functions/lines, 75% branches.\n\n**Story status:** Changed to `review` in the story file.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Branch coverage 75%:** The two `??` fallback branches in error mapping (lines 36, 38 of `schema-validate.ts`) are not exercised because ajv always provides `message` and `instancePath`. These are defensive fallbacks — not a real concern.\n- **`ajv` added as production dep, not devDep:** The story spec says \"it's a dev-time cost, not a runtime concern for a CLI tool\" but validation will run at CLI runtime (story 2.5 `validate` command), so production dep is correct. If the team disagrees, it can be moved to devDependencies and bundled by tsup.\n- **Function naming deviation:** Story spec says `validateWorkflowYaml` but I used `validateWorkflowSchema` — the function valid