p block in flow (AC #6)\" passes. Validates `{ loop: ['retry', 'verify'] }` is structurally accepted. Additional tests verify loop with empty array fails and loop with non-string items fails.\n37\t\n38\t### AC7: Missing agent field fails validation\n39\t**PASS** -- Test \"rejects missing agent in task (AC #7)\" passes. Asserts `result.valid === false`, keyword is \"required\".\n40\t\n41\t### AC8: Schema file exists at src/schemas/workflow.schema.json\n42\t**PASS** -- File exists at `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` (92 lines). Confirmed via `ls` and `wc -l`.\n43\t\n44\t### AC9: Optional fields accepted when present, pass when absent\n45\t**PASS** -- Test \"accepts optional fields when present and passes when absent (AC #9)\" passes. Tests `fullValidWorkflow()` (with prompt_template, input_contract, output_contract, source_access, max_budget_usd) and `minimalValidWorkflow()` (agent only). Both validate successfully.\n46\t\n47\t### AC10: All schema validation tests pass with 80%+ coverage\n48\t**PASS** -- 28/28 tests pass. Coverage on `schema-validate.ts`: 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines. Exceeds 80% target.\n49\t\n50\t## Additional Evidence\n51\t\n52\t### TypeScript Exports\n53\t`src/lib/schema-validate.ts` exports:\n54\t- `interface ValidationError` (path, message, keyword)\n55\t- `interface ValidationResult` (valid, errors)\n56\t- `function validateAgainstSchema` (generic, reusable)\n57\t- `function validateWorkflowSchema` (workflow-specific)\n58\t\n59\t### Error Structure\n60\tTest \"returns errors with path, message, and keyword\" verifies every error object has `path` (string), `message` (string), and `keyword` (string) properties.\n61\t\n62\t### Schema Size\n63\t`src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`: 92 lines (well under any reasonable limit).\n64\t\n65\t## Test Output (schema-validate.test.ts)\n66\t\n67\t```\n68\t28 tests passed, 0 failed\n69\t- validateWorkflowSchema > valid workflows (6 tests)\n70\t- validateWorkflowSchema > missing 