{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DE3aSTY7Yv4Z7DztvaFraR","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-02\n2\t\n3\t## Session Summary\n4\t\n5\t**Date:** 2026-04-02\n6\t**Duration:** ~18 minutes (10:07 - 10:25 UTC)\n7\t**Stories attempted:** 1\n8\t**Stories completed:** 1\n9\t\n10\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome |\n11\t|-------|-----------|---------|\n12\t| 1-2-delete-ralph-loop-legacy-verification | code-review, verification | done |\n13\t\n14\tStory 1-1-delete-beads-integration was completed in an earlier session today (07:58 - 09:45 UTC). This session only handled the final review and verification of story 1-2.\n15\t\n16\t**Sprint progress after session:** Epic 1 stories 1-1 and 1-2 both `done`. Next up: 1-3-workflow-state-module.\n17\t\n18\t---\n19\t\n20\t## Issues Analysis\n21\t\n22\t### Categorized Issues from Session Log\n23\t\n24\t**Story Spec Errors (2)**\n25\t- `src/lib/state.ts` listed for deletion in AC #3, but has 14+ importers — would break the project. Dev agent correctly skipped it.\n26\t- `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` path in story spec was wrong — actual file was at `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts`.\n27\t\n28\t**Incomplete Cleanup (2)**\n29\t- HIGH: ralph/ directory not fully deleted on disk — remaining files (.call_count, .harness-prompt.md, state files, logs) caught by code review.\n30\t- MEDIUM: `package.json` `files` array still references `ralph/**/*.sh` and `ralph/AGENTS.md` — stale entries for deleted directory.\n31\t\n32\t**Test/Coverage Issues (1)**\n33\t- MEDIUM: `run.ts` coverage dropped to 67.44% (below 80% floor) after ralph removal. Code review added 7 tests to fix.\n34\t\n35\t**Stale References (3)**\n36\t- `dashboard-formatter.ts` comment leak referencing \"ralph\"\n37\t- `stats.ts` hardcoded `ralph/logs/` path — broken after deletion\n38\t- Multiple JSDoc comments still referenced ralph/beads (fixed in code review)\n39\t\n40\t**Process Issues (1)**\n41\t- Verification proof document had wrong format — had to be rewritten to match expected `## AC N: Title` format.\n42\t\n43\t### Severity Distribution\n44\t\n45\t| Severity | Count | Fixed? |\n46\t|----------|-------|--------|\n47\t| HIGH | 1 | Yes |\n48\t| MEDIUM | 3 | 2 fixed, 1 deferred (package.json stale entries) |\n49\t| LOW | 2 | Deferred (stubs, dead test suites) |\n50\t\n51\t---\n52\t\n53\t## Cost Analysis\n54\t\n55\t### Session Tool Usage (This Session Only — Story 1-2 Review + Verification)\n56\t\n57\t`codeharness stats` could not run — ralph/session-logs directory was deleted as part of story 1-2. Cost data is reconstructed from subagent token reports in the session issues log.\n58\t\n59\t**Code Review phase (1-2):**\n60\t\n61\t| Tool | Calls |\n62\t|------|-------|\n63\t| Bash | 12 |\n64\t| Read | 13 |\n65\t| Edit | 8 |\n66\t| Grep | 3 |\n67\t| Glob | 4 |\n68\t| Skill | 1 |\n69\t| **Total** | **29** |\n70\t\n71\tLargest Bash outputs: `git diff --name-only` (~250 lines), `git ls-files ralph/` (~250 lines), `git status --porcelain` (~80 lines).\n72\t\n73\t**Verification phase (1-2):**\n74\t\n75\t| Tool | Calls |\n76\t|------|-------|\n77\t| Bash | 14 |\n78\t| Read | 3 |\n79\t| Grep | 4 |\n80\t| Write | 1 |\n81\t| **Total** | **20** |\n82\t\n83\tLargest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~30 lines), `npm run lint` (~20 lines), `npm run build` (~15 lines).\n84\t\n85\t### Session Total: 49 tool calls across 2 phases\n86\t\n87\t### Full-Day Subagent Breakdown (All of Story 1-1 + 1-2)\n88\t\n89\t| Phase | Story | Tool Calls | Heaviest Tools |\n90\t|-------|-------|-----------|----------------|\n91\t| create-story | 1-1 | 16 | Read: 8, Bash: 4 |\n92\t| dev-story | 1-1 | 67 | Edit: 28, Read: 22 |\n93\t| code-review | 1-1 | 30 | Read: 18, Edit: 9 |\n94\t| verification | 1-1 | 6 | Bash: 4, Read: 3 |\n95\t| create-story | 1-2 | 12 | Bash: 4, Read: 4 |\n96\t| dev-story | 1-2 | 53 | Edit: 28, Read: 18 |\n97\t| code-review | 1-2 | 29 | Read: 13, Bash: 12 |\n98\t| verification | 1-2 | 20 | Bash: 14, Grep: 4 |\n99\t| **Total** | | **233** | |\n100\t\n101\t### Token Waste Hotspots\n102\t\n103\t1. **`run.test.ts` read 4 times** at different offsets during 1-2 dev — file was too large for single read.\n104\t2. **Test suite run 3 times** during 1-2 dev — first two runs caught missed references.\n105\t3. **`git diff --stat HEAD~1` run twice** during 1-2 verification — redundant.\n106\t4. **1-1 dev had 2 unnecessary test re-runs** due to missed beads references in first pass.\n107\t5. **`npm run test:unit` output at ~600 lines** in 1-2 dev — largest single Bash output of the day. Should pipe through `tail` or `--silent`.\n108\t\n109\t---\n110\t\n111\t## What Went Well\n112\t\n113\t1. **Both deletion stories completed successfully.** 1-1 (beads) and 1-2 (ralph/hooks/legacy) are done. The codebase is now free of both beads and ralph dependencies.\n114\t2. **Code review caught real bugs.** The review phases found HIGH-severity issues (incomplete ralph deletion, broken stats.ts path, dead type members) that would have been shipped without review.\n115\t3. **Coverage held above floor.** 96.78% overall, all 147 remaining files above the 80% per-file minimum.\n116\t4. **Create-story risk predictions were accurate.** Both stories correctly predicted the `src/lib/state.ts` dependency problem and the scope of changes needed.\n117\t5. **Net LOC strongly negative.** -656,265 lines removed (mostly ralph/logs), achieving NFR17's code-reduction goal.\n118\t6. **Verification was fast.** Both stories passed verification on first attempt after code review fixes.\n119\t\n120\t---\n121\t\n122\t## What Went Wrong\n123\t\n124\t1. **Story spec had incorrect file path.** `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` vs actual `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` — spec was written from memory, not verified.\n125\t2. **Story spec listed `src/lib/state.ts` for deletion** despite 14+ active importers. Dev agent had to make a judgment call to skip it. This could have caused a catastrophic build failure if followed blindly.\n126\t3. **Multiple commands are now stubs/no-ops.** `run`, `applyAllPatches`, `createProofDocument`, `getDriver` — these are by design (Epic 5 rebuilds them), but it means the CLI is partially non-functional until then.\n127\t4. **`codeharness stats` is broken.** Deleting ralph/session-logs means the stats command can no longer find historical data. No cost report can be generated.\n128\t5. **Proof document format mismatch.** Verification had to rewrite the proof to match expected `## AC N: Title` format — the dev/review phases should produce proofs in the correct format.\n129\t\n130\t---\n131\t\n132\t## Lessons Learned\n133\t\n134\t### Patterns to Repeat\n135\t\n136\t- **Create-story risk identification works.** Both stories flagged the real problems before dev started. Keep using the risk analysis step.\n137\t- **Code review as a separate phase catches real issues.** The HIGH-severity ralph directory cleanup miss and the stats.ts broken path were both caught here, not in dev.\n138\t- **Pure-deletion stories with `test-provable` ACs are efficient.** Both stories moved quickly because the acceptance criteria were binary (code exists or it doesn't).\n139\t\n140\t### Patterns to Avoid\n141\t\n142\t- **Story specs listing files for deletion without verifying import count.** Always run `grep -r \"from.*module\"` before listing a file for deletion.\n143\t- **Large test file reads at multiple offsets.** `run.test.ts` was read 4 times. Consider splitting large test files or using targeted grep instead.\n144\t- **Running full test suite without `--silent` or `tail`.** 600-line test output is wasteful. Pipe through `tail -20` unless debugging.\n145\t- **Assuming the stats command will work after deleting its data source.** Should have saved stats before deleting ralph.\n146\t\n147\t---\n148\t\n149\t## Action Items\n150\t\n151\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n152\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n153\t| 1 | Fix `package.json` `files` array — remove stale `ralph/**/*.sh` and `ralph/AGENTS.md` entries | HIGH | Next session |\n154\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness stats` to handle missing session-logs directory gracefully | MEDIUM | Epic 5 or standalone fix |\n155\t| 3 | Add validation to `create-story` skill: verify file deletion targets have zero importers before listing | MEDIUM | Process improvement |\n156\t| 4 | Clean up `describe.skip('importOnboardingEpic — removed')` in `epic-generator.test.ts` | LOW | Tech debt |\n157\t| 5 | Remove `--keep-beads` and `--keep-ralph` CLI flags from teardown command if still present | LOW | Tech debt |\n158\t| 6 | Begin story 1-3-workflow-state-module — next in sprint plan | HIGH | Next session |\n159\t\n160\t---\n161\t\n162\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-02 (Session 2: Story 1-3)\n163\t\n164\t**Generated:** 2026-04-02T11:10 UTC\n165\t\n166\t## 1. Session Summary\n167\t\n168\t**Date:** 2026-04-02\n169\t**Duration:** ~28 minutes (approx 10:40 - 11:08 UTC)\n170\t**Stories attempted:** 1\n171\t**Stories completed:** 1\n172\t**Epic 1 status:** DONE (3/3 stories complete)\n173\t\n174\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Commit |\n175\t|-------|-----------|---------|--------|\n176\t| 1-3-workflow-state-module | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | done | `39ec40c` |\n177\t\n178\tThis session completed the final story in Epic 1 (v2 Foundation Cleanup). The workflow-state module provides YAML-based persistence for workflow execution state — a building block for Epic 5 (flow execution engine). Epic 1 is now fully closed.\n179\t\n180\t---\n181\t\n182\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n183\t\n184\t### Categorized Issues from Session Log\n185\t\n186\t**Spec/Config Gaps (2)**\n187\t- `workflow.yaml` vs `workflow.md` naming inconsistency in skill trigger configuration.\n188\t- No `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` or `project-context.md` found — create-story agent had to infer context from existing artifacts.\n189\t\n190\t**Code Quality Issues Found by Review (3)**\n191\t- **HIGH:** `readState`/`writeState` naming collision with existing `state.ts` module — renamed to `readWorkflowState`/`writeWorkflowState`. Fixed.\n192\t- **MEDIUM:** `isValidWorkflowState` did not validate `tasks_completed` element shapes, `evaluator_scores`, or `score_history` element types. Fixed — 6 tests added.\n193\t- **LOW (deferred):** Branch coverage at 72.22%, stale AGENTS.md entries from stories 1-1/1-2.\n194\t\n195\t**Test/Coverage Observations (2)**\n196\t- AC #3 \"state survives process exit\" tested via separate function calls, not actual OS process restarts — weaker guarantee but sufficient for unit tests.\n197\t- Statement coverage at 80% meets AC; branch coverage at 73.52% below the 80% aspiration but not a blocker.\n198\t\n199\t**Process Notes (2)**\n200\t- Sprint-status.yaml update skipped per orchestrator instructions (correct behavior).\n201\t- New module uses plain YAML, diverging from existing `state.ts` which uses markdown-wrapped YAML — intentional per architecture-v2.md.\n202\t\n203\t### Severity Distribution\n204\t\n205\t| Severity | Count | Fixed? |\n206\t|----------|-------|--------|\n207\t| HIGH | 1 | Yes (naming collision) |\n208\t| MEDIUM | 2 | Yes (validation gaps) |\n209\t| LOW | 2 | Deferred |\n210\t\n211\t---\n212\t\n213\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n214\t\n215\t### Session Token Report (Aggregated from Subagent Reports)\n216\t\n217\t`codeharness stats` unavailable (session-logs directory was deleted in story 1-2). Data below is reconstructed from the four subagent token reports in `.session-issues.md`.\n218\t\n219\t**Aggregate Tool Usage Across All 4 Phases:**\n220\t\n221\t| Tool | create-story | dev-story | code-review | verification | Total |\n222\t|------|-------------|-----------|-------------|--------------|-------|\n223\t| Bash | 5 | 8 | 11 | 9 | **33** |\n224\t| Read | 9 | 7 | 7 | 3 | **26** |\n225\t| Edit | 0 | 4 | 10 | 0 | **14** |\n226\t| Write | 1 | 2 | 0 | 1 | **4** |\n227\t| Grep | 2 | 0 | 1 | 0 | **3** |\n228\t| Glob | 4 | 2 | 1 | 0 | **7** |\n229\t| Skill | 1 | 1 | 1 | 0 | **3** |\n230\t| **Total** | **16** | **20** | **24** | **14** | **74** |\n231\t\n232\t**Files Read:** 31 unique reads across session (10 + 10 + 9 + 3 = 32 total reads, ~31 unique files).\n233\t\n234\t### Subagent-Level Breakdown\n235\t\n236\t**Phase 1 — create-story (16 calls):** Mostly Read (9) to gather context. Clean — zero redundant operations reported. Heaviest output was `ls implementation-artifacts/` at ~170 lines.\n237\t\n238\t**Phase 2 — dev-story (20 calls):** Implementation phase. Coverage command run 3 times (initial run, after adding test, to extract line numbers). This is the only reported redundancy. Test suite outputs were small (~10-140 lines).\n239\t\n240\t**Phase 3 — code-review (24 calls):** Most tool-intensive phase. Edit-heavy (10 edits) — fixed naming collision, validation gaps, added 6 tests. Three consecutive grep attempts for coverage data (redundant). The review found and fixed real issues, so the cost was justified.\n241\t\n242\t**Phase 4 — verification (14 calls):** Lean. Ran `codeharness verify` twice and had multiple ANSI-stripping attempts for coverage parsing. Otherwise efficient.\n243\t\n244\t### Token Waste Hotspots\n245\t\n246\t1. **Coverage command run 3x in dev-story** — could have been 1-2x with better sequencing.\n247\t2. **3 consecutive grep attempts for coverage data in code-review** — tooling should parse coverage output in one pass.\n248\t3. **`codeharness verify` run twice in verification** — first run may have had output parsing issues.\n249\t4. **Multiple ANSI-stripping attempts** — coverage output formatting is a recurring friction point.\n250\t\n251\t### Comparison with Previous Session\n252\t\n253\t| Metric | Session 1 (stories 1-1, 1-2) | Session 2 (story 1-3) |\n254\t|--------|-------------------------------|----------------------|\n255\t| Stories | 2 | 1 |\n256\t| Total tool calls | 233 | 74 |\n257\t| Calls per story | ~117 | 74 |\n258\t| Duration | ~18 min (review+verify only for 1-2) | ~28 min (full lifecycle) |\n259\t| Phases | 8 total | 4 total |\n260\t\n261\tStory 1-3 was more efficient per-phase than 1-1/1-2 (18.5 calls/phase vs 29 calls/phase), likely because it was a greenfield module with no deletion archaeology.\n262\t\n263\t### Historical Cost Context\n264\t\n265\tFrom the cumulative cost report (all sessions): $900.92 total across 6,568 API calls for 158 stories. Average $4.17/story. The verify phase alone accounts for 53.1% of all cost — this remains the dominant cost center and a target for optimization.\n266\t\n267\t---\n268\t\n269\t## 4. What Went Well\n270\t\n271\t1. **Full story lifecycle in ~28 minutes.** Create-story through verification, including a code review that found and fixed real issues.\n272\t2. **Code review caught a naming collision (HIGH).** `readState`/`writeState` would have conflicted with the existing `state.ts` module at import time. Caught and fixed before merge.\n273\t3. **Code review caught validation gaps (MEDIUM).** Array element type validation was missing in `isValidWorkflowState` — added 6 tests for edge cases.\n274\t4. **Clean, self-contained module.** 151 lines of source, 392 lines of tests. Zero internal dependencies except `output.ts` for `warn()`. This is how new v2 modules should look.\n275\t5. **Epic 1 fully complete.** All 3 foundation cleanup stories done. The codebase is cleaned up and has its first v2 module in place.\n276\t6. **Efficient tool usage.** 74 total calls is lean for a full 4-phase story lifecycle.\n277\t\n278\t---\n279\t\n280\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n281\t\n282\t1. **No cost tracking possible.** `codeharness stats` broken because session-logs/ was deleted in story 1-2. Had to reconstruct from subagent token reports manually.\n283\t2. **Branch coverage below 80%.** At 73.52%, the uncovered branches are internal validation paths in `isValidWorkflowState()` that are hard to trigger through the public API. Not a blocker but a known gap.\n284\t3. **AC #3 persistence test is weaker than ideal.** Tests verify state survives function call boundaries, not actual OS process exits. True cross-process testing would require spawning child processes.\n285\t4. **Stale AGENTS.md entries from stories 1-1/1-2.** Deferred as LOW but accumulating tech debt.\n286\t5. **Coverage output parsing remains fragile.** Multiple ANSI-stripping attempts and repeated grep runs across phases — this is a systemic friction point.\n287\t\n288\t---\n289\t\n290\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n291\t\n292\t### Patterns to Repeat\n293\t\n294\t- **Greenfield modules are fast.** No deletion archaeology, no import-chain analysis. Story 1-3 was 74 calls vs ~117/story for deletion stories.\n295\t- **Code review as a separate phase continues to pay off.** The naming collision would have been a runtime bug. The validation gaps would have been exploitable.\n296\t- **Plain YAML for new state files.** The markdown-wrapped YAML in `state.ts` is legacy. New modules using plain YAML are simpler to read, write, and validate.\n297\t- **Self-contained modules with minimal dependencies.** `workflow-state.ts` depends only on `output.ts`. This makes testing trivial and reduces blast radius.\n298\t\n299\t### Patterns to Avoid\n300\t\n301\t- **Running coverage commands multiple times per phase.** Dev-story ran it 3x, code-review tried grep 3x. Establish a pattern: run once, capture output, parse from captured output.\n302\t- **Deleting data sources before saving their data.** Story 1-2 deleted ralph/session-logs before `codeharness stats --save` could run. Always save before delete.\n303\t- **Relying on ANSI-aware parsing for coverage output.** Either strip ANSI at the source (run with `--no-color`) or build a robust strip function.\n304\t\n305\t---\n306\t\n307\t## 7. Action Items\n308\t\n309\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n310\t|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n311\t| 1 | Fix `codeharness stats` to handle missing session-logs directory | HIGH | Standalone fix or Epic 5 | Carried from Session 1 |\n312\t| 2 | Fix `package.json` `files` array — remove stale `ralph/**/*.sh` and `ralph/AGENTS.md` entries | HIGH | Next session | Carried from Session 1 |\n313\t| 3 | Clean up stale AGENTS.md entries from stories 1-1/1-2 | LOW | Tech debt | New |\n314\t| 4 | Add `--no-color` flag to all `vitest --coverage` invocations in subagent prompts | MEDIUM | Process improvement | New |\n315\t| 5 | Establish \"run coverage once, parse from captured output\" pattern in dev-story skill | MEDIUM | Process improvement | New |\n316\t| 6 | Begin Epic 2 (workflow YAML schema and parser) | HIGH | Next sprint session | New |\n317\t| 7 | Consider adding true cross-process persistence test for workflow-state (spawn child process) | LOW | Tech debt | New |\n318\t\n319\t---\n320\t\n321\t### Epic 1 Final Scorecard\n322\t\n323\t| Story | Tool Calls | Key Issues Found | Outcome |\n324\t|-------|-----------|-----------------|---------|\n325\t| 1-1-delete-beads-integration | ~119 | Dead type members, stale JSDoc | done |\n326\t| 1-2-delete-ralph-loop-legacy-verification | ~114 | Incomplete ralph/ deletion, broken stats.ts path | done |\n327\t| 1-3-workflow-state-module | 74 | Naming collision, validation gaps | done |\n328\t| **Epic Total** | **~307** | 8 issues found by review | **DONE** |\n329\t\n330\tEpic 1 achieved its goal: remove legacy subsystems (beads, ralph, legacy verification) and establish the first v2 module (workflow-state). The codebase is cleaner (-656K LOC from ralph alone) and ready for Epic 2.\n331\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014qEcGGsz3MiamcyEZEG8mM","session_id":"c54cfa66-957c-4f2c-a205-da1113d93a9b","uuid":"feb40b21-4f00-47cc-ae89-967473a2bf00","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:22:35.790Z"}
